(42, 15, 1, 26, 18, 27, 27, 'sinners for to hear him', 'Repentance and Acceptance', 'This connection highlights the theme of turning away from wickedness and seeking righteousness. Both passages emphasize the importance of sinners approaching God for redemption and the possibility of salvation through repentance.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 15, 1, 40, 21, 28, 31, 'publicans and sinners', 'Repentance and Acceptance Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of repentance and acceptance of sinners. In Luke, publicans and sinners are drawn to Jesus, while in Matthew, the first son represents those who initially reject but later repent, illustrating that those deemed sinful can enter the kingdom of God.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 15, 1, 42, 7, 29, 29, 'publicans', 'Publicans and Sinners Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of publicans, indicating their role in responding to Jesus'' message. The publicans in both verses illustrate a broader theme of marginalized individuals drawn to Jesus.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 15, 1, 45, 5, 20, 20, 'publicans and sinners', 'Grace Abounding in Sinners', 'This connection highlights the presence of sinners in both passages. In Luke, publicans and sinners are drawn to Jesus, while Romans emphasizes that where sin abounds, grace abounds even more.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 15, 2, 40, 9, 11, 11, 'eateth with them', 'Pharisees'' Criticism of Jesus', 'This connection highlights the Pharisees'' criticism of Jesus for associating with sinners. Both passages emphasize their disapproval of Jesus eating with those labeled as sinners.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
